title: Ian Bell lauds Alastair Cook's batting "masterclass" against Pakistan - Thewestmorland Gazette
text:
Ian Bell congratulated his captain Alastair Cook on a "masterclass" unbeaten century as England tried to navigate a draw in the first Test against Pakistan. Bell, who like Pakistan bowling coach Mushtaq Ahmed conceded the surface in Abu Dhabi was perhaps not conducive to Test cricket at its best, had no doubt that Cook played the conditions to a tee.
